description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity currently exists for experienced Registered Nurses to join the Urgent Public Health Research team based at the Queen Alexandra Hospital for an initial period of 3 to 6 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During this challenging time, Registered Nurses will be working as part of a team delivering high quality clinical research for the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking RN’s with diverse acute ward experience, ideally having worked within Respiratory High Care or ‘Covid’ wards. Phlebotomy experience is also desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities include but are no means limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Contributing to the coordination and delivery of Clinical Trial activities within Portsmouth Hospitals University NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          Assisting with the review of new Trial protocols and contribute to the assessment of their clinical and practical implications to local patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          To assist in the management of the local requirements for a number of approved Clinical Trial protocols.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-          To assist in the identification, screening and assessment of the suitability of local patients to take part in Clinical Trials, in accordance with specified inclusion/exclusion criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is initially for a 3-6 month period, with ongoing day shifts that could also include weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this critical post, please submit your most recent CV at your earliest convenience.&lt;/p&gt;
